#: ../../content/documents/index.md:1
msgid "Resident documents"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:4
msgid ""
"The automatic document folder for every nursing home (MR/MRS) resident: "
"subfolders, tags, and the Documents button on the record."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:8
msgid "Where is a resident's document folder located?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:9
msgid ""
"In Odoo's Documents app, under the \"Residents\" folder. The easiest way:"
" open the resident's record and click the \"Documents\" button — it opens"
" their personal folder directly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:11
msgid "Do I have to create the folder and subfolders myself?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:12
msgid ""
"No. Resthome creates the resident's personal folder and its three "
"subfolders (Medical, Administrative, and Billing documents) "
"automatically, as soon as the resident is created or their resident "
"record is activated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:14
msgid "What does the number shown on the \"Documents\" button count?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:15
msgid ""
"The number of files stored in the resident's folder, subfolders included."
" The subfolders themselves are not counted, only the documents they "
"contain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:17
msgid "Can I delete a resident folder by mistake?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:18
msgid ""
"No. Automatically created folders are protected: a standard user can drop"
" documents into them and view them, but cannot delete the folder itself."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:20
msgid "What are tags like Katz, eAgreement, or GDPR for?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:21
msgid ""
"They are ready-to-use tags for categorizing documents and finding them by"
" filter in the Documents app. You can also apply some of them "
"automatically through the settings (\"Default tags\")."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:23
msgid "Does each facility have its own folders?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:24
msgid ""
"Yes. In multi-company, each facility has its own \"Residents\" root "
"folder and its own \"Blank forms\" folder, which keeps documents "
"separated per home."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:27
msgid ""
"For **each resident**, Resthome maintains a **document folder** stored in"
" Odoo's **Documents** app. You have nothing to create or file by hand: "
"the folder, its subfolders, and the filing are automatic. You access it "
"from the **Documents** button on the resident's record, or from the "
"**Documents → Residents** app."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:32
msgid "Prerequisite"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:35
msgid ""
"This feature relies on Odoo's **Documents** app: it must be installed. "
"Once enabled, the resident folders and tags are set up automatically — "
"you have nothing to prepare."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:40
msgid "One folder per resident, created automatically"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:42
msgid ""
"As soon as a resident is created (or as soon as their record becomes a "
"resident record), Resthome creates their **personal folder** under the "
"**\"Residents\"** root folder, with **three ready-to-use subfolders**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:46
msgid "Subfolder"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:46
msgid "What goes in it"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:46
msgid "**Medical documents**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:46
msgid "The resident's assessments, forms, and medical items."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:46
msgid "**Administrative documents**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:46
msgid "Convention, ID documents, agreements, letters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:46
msgid "**Billing documents**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:46
msgid "Invoices and items related to the resident's billing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:61
msgid ""
"The folder is named after the **resident's name** and **renames itself "
"automatically** if the name changes. Folders are **sorted "
"alphabetically**, which keeps them easy to browse in the Documents app."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:65
msgid "Protected folders"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:68
msgid ""
"Automatically created folders are **protected from deletion**: a standard"
" user can drop documents into them and view them, but cannot delete the "
"folder itself. This keeps you from accidentally losing a resident's "
"entire document structure."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:75
msgid "The \"Documents\" button on the record"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:77
msgid ""
"On the resident's record, a **\"Documents\" smart button** shows the "
"**number of files** stored in their folder. The counter adds up the "
"documents in the folder **and its subfolders** (the subfolders themselves"
" are not counted). Clicking the button **opens** the resident's personal "
"folder directly in the Documents app."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:82
msgid "Only for Documents app users"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:85
msgid ""
"The button only appears for users who have access to the **Documents** "
"app. Others still see the resident record normally, without the shortcut."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:91
msgid "Folders created at the facility level"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:93
msgid ""
"When the company (the facility) is created, Resthome automatically sets "
"up two folders at the top of the Documents app:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:96
msgid "**Residents** — the root folder that contains all resident folders."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:97
msgid ""
"**Blank forms** — a subfolder for your **templates** and documents to "
"fill in (standard conventions, blank medical forms, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:100
msgid "Separated by facility"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:103
msgid ""
"In multi-company, **each facility has its own root folder** \"Residents\""
" and its own \"Blank forms\" folder. Documents therefore stay separated "
"from one home to another."
msgstr ""

