#: ../../content/documents/index.md:125
msgid "Apply tags automatically"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:128
msgid ""
"You can have one or more of these tags applied **automatically** to every"
" centralized document, through the **Default tags** field in the "
"settings. See [Document settings](../configuration/reglages-"
"documents.md)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:133
msgid "Automatic filing of attachments"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:135
msgid ""
"Beyond the folders, Resthome can **automatically centralize** attachments"
" dropped on a resident's record: they land directly in their personal "
"folder, with no manual filing. This behavior is set in the configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:139
msgid "Learn more"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:142
msgid ""
"The detailed behavior, use cases, and activation are described on the "
"[Document centralization](centralisation.md) page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:146
msgid "Key points to remember"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:148
msgid ""
"Each resident has an **automatic personal folder** with three subfolders:"
" **medical**, **administrative**, **billing**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:150
msgid ""
"The folder follows the **resident's name** and renames itself; folders "
"are **protected from accidental deletion**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:152
msgid ""
"The record's **\"Documents\" button** opens the folder and counts the "
"files, subfolders included."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:154
msgid ""
"At the facility level, Resthome creates the **\"Residents\"** and "
"**\"Blank forms\"** folders, **separated per company**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/documents/index.md:156
msgid ""
"Nine predefined **tags** (Katz, eAgreement, GDPR, CPAS…) make filtering "
"easier, and can be applied automatically."
msgstr ""

